    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">652.113 Auto/67</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Spanish Minister for Foreign Affairs (<persName
                            type="from">de los Ríos</persName>) to the American Ambassador in Spain
                            (<persName type="to">Bowers</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="30" xml:id="d511fn30">Copy transmitted to the Department by the
                        Ambassador in his despatch No. 70, July 12; received July 26.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 112</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-08">July 8,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge to your
                    Excellency receipt of his note of the 5th instant by which he wishes to
                    ascertain the effect (<hi rend="italic">alcance</hi>) which the “avenant”
                    concluded between Spain and France has on the importation into our country of
                    automobiles of French manufacture.</p>
                <p>The terms of the Agreement entered into with France are those which have been
                    published in full in the <hi rend="italic">Gaceta de Madrid</hi> for June 23rd
                    last, Possibly some newspapers, while dealing with a hypothetical (<hi
                        rend="italic">supuesta</hi>) reduction of the customs tariff applicable to
                    French automobiles, refer to the possibility that France may request a reduction
                    of certain customs tariffs which the present Spanish regulations make it
                    possible to grant in favor of foreign countries whose consumption of our basic
                    products of exportation attain a certain proportion; tariff advantages that can
                    be made effective by virtue of the so-called policy of “benefits” (<hi
                        rend="italic">retornos</hi>) and can be requested by all the nations which,
                    as buyers of Spanish products, may find themselves in the same position as
                    France.</p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>(By direction) <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Gómez Ocerín</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
